rComments: She relates to students and is very helpful. Had her for a summer course. one of the best Profs i've had

She is absolutely amazing. She talks fast, but I never fell asleep in any of her 3 hour lectures. She makes the dry materials interesting, and the tests were fair. If you go to lecture, take notes, and study, A+ is not impossible.
She's fair, but she thinks and acts too much like a researcher that's being bothered by novices. Class is stimulating and entertaining, but tests were a little much for a 200 class.

After four years at U of T and taking three courses with her, I can say that Hana is the best professor I've had. She's funny, makes lectures fun, and is very fair. If you have a chance to take ANY course she's teaching, take it. I assure you that you won't regret it!!

Hana is amazing. If you have a chance to take her course, take it. If you have her, consider yourself lucky. If our course text was the phonebook, I'm sure Professor Burianova would find a way to make it interesting. She's pretty kick back, but be warned she can crack the whip. Best prof. I've had so far, ever...
hanna is an amazing professor, her lectures are full of visuals and examples to help you remember the concepts. she keeps her lectures upbeat and interesting even when they stretch into three hours
Hana is the best and she is sooooo cute i hope i get 4.o
Actual material is dry, but her lectures are fun and interesting

Hana is an absolutely wonderful teacher.  The first prof that I felt I could approach for any little question I had.  She makes class interesting.  Her personal examples help create a connection between prof and students.  The fact that she has experience with some of the issues makes her even more knowledgeable.  Wish the class wasn't almost over!

She makes class very fun and enjoyable...she definitely seems to be a "students' prof" (if such a term exists) in that she really seems to empathize with her students and understands many of the issues we face probably b/c she was in our position not too long ago herself. Overall cool prof and mildly interesting course!
She is a great. She very knowledgeable and works really hard to make the material interesting for students. UofT is lucky to have her.

HOLY COW, talk about having a knack for teaching. This prof can relate to students and motivate them. Clear delivery of material and goes beyond the textbook to extend our thinking. Such a great skill to learn. I highly recommend Hana, she's wonderful!!!!!
Interesting lectures.  Vry passionate about material.  Inspired critical thinking.
She is a great professor. She made the class interesting and ejoyable. I would take classes with her again.
she is such an easygoing professor and really made the course enjoyable.  The material was so borring but with her helpful slides and fun lectures it really wasnt that hard to study for this course.
What a great prof.  Available, approachable, feedback everywhere you turn, and really likes teaching and likes her students.  Take any class she teaches, it's a pleasure to have her.
Hana is a great prof!  She uses a variety of evaluation methods and her tests mostly consist of lecture material, so the readings are not that important.  I really enjoyed both her classes!
